<refentry id="kaenvironmentsv">

  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>kaenv</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>
  
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>kaenv</refname>
    <refpurpose> list, add or remove an environment </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  


  <refsect1>
    <title>SYNOPSIS</title>
    <command>kaenv</command>
    <para>
      <command>--add</command> Want to add an environment
    </para>
    <para>
      <command>--del</command> Want to del an environment
    </para>
    <para>
      <command>--list</command> Want to list all environment
    </para>

    <para>
      <command>-e environmentname</command> environment name
    </para>
    <para>
      <command>-l login</command> login of environment
    </para>

    <para>
      <command>-m host</command> host to scan
    </para>
    <para>
      <command>-h|--help</command> help screen.
    </para>
    
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      kaenv register, display and delete environment from the database.
      It is a simple environment referencing system.
      You can see the environment of another user with <emphasis>-l</emphasis>.
    </para>
    <para>
      kaenv doesn't check the syntax of the environment file.      
      kadeploy will try to detect error in the file but will deploy what is describe...
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>DEPLOYMENT CLASS
    </title>
    <para>
      kadeploy manage four class of deployment system : 
    </para>
    <para>
      - pxelinux system (linux + initrd)
    </para>
    <para>
      - Linux system with tar and ext3 fs
    </para>
    <para>
      - Windows 2000 and XP with fat32 fs
    </para>
    <para>
      - raw partition with bootsector included
    </para>
    <para>
      
    </para>

  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>ENVIRONMENT FILE
    </title>

    <para>
      <command>pxe linux deployment example</command>
    </para>
    <para>
deploytype=pxelinux
    </para>
    <para>
kernel=/pathto/vmlinuz      
    </para>
    <para>
initrd=/pathto/initrd
    </para>
    <para>
kernelparams=init=/bin/sh
    </para>



    <para>
      <command>linux deployment example</command>
    </para>
    <para>
deploytype=linux
    </para>
    <para>
basefile=/pathto/basefile.tgz
    </para>
    <para>
postinstall=/pathto/postinstall.tgz
      </para>
    <para>
kernel=/pathto/vmlinuz
    </para>
    <para>
initrd=/pathto/initrd.img
      </para>
    <para>
kernelparams=init=/bin/sh
      </para>
    <para>



      <command>dd deployment example</command>
    </para>
    <para>
deploytype=dd
    </para>
    <para>
basefile=/pathtobasefile.tgz
    </para>
    <para>



      <command>windows deployment example</command>
    </para>
    <para>
deploytype=windows
    </para>
    <para>
basefile=/pathtobasefile.tgz
    </para>
    <para>
windowsbootdirectory=WINDOWS
    </para>

  </refsect1>
      
  <refsect1>
    <title>EXAMPLE</title>
    <command> kaenv --list</command>  
    <para> display all the environment.</para>

    <command> kaenv --del -e debian -l yoyz</command>  
    <para> remove the environment debian for the current user.</para>

    <command> kaenv --add -e debian4all -l yoyz -f $(pwd)/debian4all.env</command>  
    <para> register the environment debian4all with the user yoyz.</para>
  </refsect1>

